President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of West Virginia due to severe storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from April 13-15, 2015. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Cabell, Calhoun, Greenbrier, Jackson, Pleasants, Roane, Summers, and Wirt are eligible for federal funding for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures statewide are also eligible for federal funding. Kari Suzann Cowie has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area, and additional designations may be made if requested by the state and warranted by further damage assessments.